Rating: 4
Probably redundant to rate an already noted outstanding recipe. But, they are so good. Crust is flaky and crisp. For any pastry with a jam filling, I reduce the jam by simmering it a few minutes. It doesn't usually leak and the taste is not affected at all. I thought the dough was a little thick, so rolled it 12" x 12" and cut 3"x4" rectangles making 12 tarts. They were perfect. Emily, in Michigan

