Rating: 4
These were so delicious. I made them two nights in a row because my friends wanted to come back for more! I used a bit less salt and a bit more sugar for the pastry, and made them into small triangles the second time as an experiment, since they seemed to fall apart a bit too easily as rectangles. Great either way, and I will definitely try other fruits next time. I also sprinkled them with raw sugar before baking instead of powdered sugar after.

Rating: 4
I made these with farm fresh strawberry preserves and it came out great. Here's what I changed: -I made them smaller than the recipe called for, since I knew they would crumble easily and would be less messy if they were smaller. -I trimmed the edges of the dough after I put the second layer on. I then re-rolled this dough to make a few more pastries. -I plan to use slightly less salt and slightly more sugar next time. DELICIOUS! Will make double next time.

