Rating: 4
I have been looking for a pastry recipe to make prune danish. These delightful little pockets were perfect for a prune filling. Stewed the prunes with a little sugar, then pureed and used instead of fruit preserves. Just ate one with a cup of tea. Awesome. Crust is so flaky and tender. Cooked in 365 degree convection oven for 16 minutes and brushed with a touch of heavy cream for nice browning. This one is going on my blog!

